g_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Tumblr is betting big on going small", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Tumblr logo on a pink and purple background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/V9s3NWknMlUhre6uynnq28E1DjU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72875398/STK137_Tumblr_K_Radtke_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The social network failed to hit the growth targets its new owner set in 2019. But were they ever compatible with what Tumblr does best?</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23964580/tumblr-downscaling-smaller-social-media-site\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23964580/tumblr-downscaling-smaller-social-media-site", "date_published": "2023-11-17T14:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Tires are saving us \u2014 and killing us, too", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Conceptual illustration showing grass growing from a tire\u2019s skid mark, intended to show the possibility of a future with abundant sustainably made tires.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ThRa1cxlGgEtduIhQ6q6-iREisk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72871431/236801_Sustainable_Tires_Nico_Brausch.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nico H. Brausch for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HkpIJy\">Tires are the most important safety component on a car, yet there\u2019s increasing research that they\u2019re doing a good deal of harm, too. Slowly, surely, one mote of black dust at a time, tires are leaving their mark on the environment. </p>\n<p id=\"7MzTK3\"><a href=\"https://spiral.imperial.ac.uk/bitstream/10044/1/101707/9/Tyre%20wear%20particles%20are%20toxic%20for%20us%20and%20the%20environment%200223-2.pdf\">According to researchers at Imperial College London</a>, our cars and trucks emit 6 million tons of tire wear p", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23951181/tires-sustainable-rubber-bridgestone-michelin", "date_published": "2023-11-17T13:45:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The secret environmental cost hiding inside your smart home device", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Conceptual illustration showing a home in the hallway of a large server room. There is a haze coming from the servers to imply the environmental footprint of having a smart home.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/i4_-hNKB_BlCDnrvO564hMmIU-I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72871430/236801_Dirty_AI_Nico_Brausch.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nico H. Brausch for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"4DRYor\">Vijay Janapa Reddi runs a lab at Harvard University where he and his team attempt to solve some of the computer world\u2019s greatest challenges. As a specialist in artificial intelligence systems, the technology he studies even follows him home, where his two daughters love to talk to their Amazon Alexa. </p>\n<p id=\"DHyUyu\">\u201cThey put a person inside that black box,\u201d Janapa Reddi likes to joke with his four-year-old.</p>\n<p id=\"Tmp94e\">Janapa Reddi may be teasing when he tells his daughter a person is ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23951196/smart-home-ai-data-electricity-fossil-fuel-climate-change", "date_published": "2023-11-17T13:15:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Discord is shutting down its AI chatbot Clyde", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Discord logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PjjcyNz3po95lPcUSFhbT9bcQZ8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72874888/acastro_STK062_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zWMIXS\">Discord is shutting down Clyde, its experimental AI chatbot. In a <a href=\"https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/13066317497239-Clyde-Discord-s-AI-Chatbot\">support note</a>, Discord says the chatbot will be \u201cdeactivated\u201d at the end of the month, and that by December 1st \u201cusers will no longer be able to invoke Clyde in DMs, Group DMs or server chats.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"GcAu7C\">Discord first started testing Clyde\u2019s AI features earlier this year, using OpenAI\u2019s models to let the chatbot answer questions and have conversations with Discord users. It has been in limited testing ever since, and the company had planned to make it a fundamental part of its chat and comm", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23965185/discord-is-shutting-down-its-ai-chatbot-clyde", "date_published": "2023-11-17T10:47:09+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Bellroy\u2019s iPhone 15 Pro case has a proper Action Button now", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Close-up of side of case showing action and volume buttons.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4fxWt7sfz0xoEkcq3Vo1de_Lo3g=/0x0:3200x2133/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72874846/bellroy_pcxi_terracotta_print_04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A traditional button in place of a cutout.</em> | Image: Bellroy</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"080fcy\">Two months after some case makers were wrong-footed by Apple\u2019s decision to replace the mute switch with an Action Button on the iPhone 15 Pro lineup, Bellroy has released an <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fbellroy.com%2Fproducts%2Fphone-case%3Fcolor%3Dblack%26material%3Dleather%26size%3Di15promax%23slide-0&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F11%2F17%2F23965171%2Fbellroy-iphone-15-pro-case-action-button-cutout\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">updated</a> <a href=\"https://go.redir", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23965171/bellroy-iphone-15-pro-case-action-button-cutout", "date_published": "2023-11-17T09:36:14+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "A huge stable Steam Deck update gives the Dock a brand-new feature", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Steam Deck Dock\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/y1ei103hfuTCJzVcALdxNbrSGI0=/391x0:2500x1406/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72874172/steamdeckdockback.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Valve</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"V7KU2a\">Valve\u2019s new <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951655/steam-deck-oled-review\">Steam Deck OLED</a> just went on sale today, but there are goodies for the original LCD model, too \u2014 the company is <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/1675200/view/5484882897552407488\">now rolling out a stable build of SteamOS 3.5.5</a> with a hefty list of fixes, changes, and upgrades.</p>\n<p id=\"ZbhI6k\">Some of the biggest are ones we\u2019ve already seen <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/15/23875824/valve-steam-deck-steamos-3-5-preview-vrr-hdr-starfield\">in a September beta</a>, like support for VRR and HDR external displays, the ability to tweak your screen\u2019s color and undervolt your processor with ne", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/16/23964870/steam-deck-steamos-3-5-5-stable-update", "date_published": "2023-11-17T02:10:41+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Fortnite is blocking some outfits in experiences made for kids", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Characters in Fortnite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DQTZGT1fni-nFzyImdatWvqvWgE=/48x0:944x597/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72874170/fortnite_ratings_header_1900x600_3f43197feac0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"exSLBO\"><em>Fortnite</em> just started showing age ratings for every experience you can play in the game, but 